## Pipeline Bug Fixes 
During execution, it was reported that [run_pipeline.py](file:///c:/HelioX/run_pipeline.py) stopped providing proper answers and instead repeatedly returned the fallback answer: `"Insufficient evidence to fully answer this query."`

*   **QueryDecomposer Integration:** The mock implementation of [QueryAnalyzer](file:///c:/HelioX/query_pipeline/analyzer.py#35-183) in [run_pipeline.py](file:///c:/HelioX/run_pipeline.py) was hard-coding the `fact_components` to the raw user query. I integrated the [QueryDecomposer](file:///c:/HelioX/query_pipeline/decomposer.py#70-168) (powered by Mistral) to generate proper keyword and sub-task separation.
*   **Punctuation Stripping in Coverage Score:** The `fact_components_addressed` coverage scores were artificially 0.0 because the matching algorithms were attempting to match keywords like `heliox?` (including trailing punctuation) against the claim text. I added a `re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', '', fc.lower())` sanitizer to [synthesis/synthesizer.py](file:///c:/HelioX/synthesis/synthesizer.py), [workers/worker.py](file:///c:/HelioX/workers/worker.py), and [retrieval/dynamic_k.py](file:///c:/HelioX/retrieval/dynamic_k.py) which resolved the string-matching failure.
*   The coverage score properly hits `1.0` for valid queries again.

## Next Steps

To connect this to your Python backend:
1.  In [frontend/src/services/api.js](file:///c:/HelioX/frontend/src/services/api.js), replace the mock [submitQuery](file:///c:/HelioX/frontend/src/services/api.js#8-99) with an `axios.post` call to the FastAPI server.
2.  Enable CORS in your FastAPI `main.py` allowing `http://localhost:5173`.
3.  Ensure your backend is ready to accept the `documents` array inside the request body if they are uploaded via the frontend.
